"title": "5594: tribute",
"media_type": "Text",
"index_reference": "5594: tribute",
"language": "eng",
"review_level": "None",
"content": "<p>Gifts and honours paid as a mark of respect and submission to kings and others in authority; also, praise given to those to whom it is due.</p>\n<h2>Tribute required by God</h2>\n<h3>The spoils of war</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Num31:28\">NUM 31:28</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Num31:29\">NUM 31:29</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Num31:36-Num31:41\">NUM 31:36–31:41</a></p>\n<h3>The glory due to his name</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps96:7-Ps96:9\">PSA 96:7–96:9</a></strong>; <strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Heb13:15\">HEB 13:15</a></strong></p>\n<h2>Tribute paid to kings</h2>\n<h3>Eglon, king of Moab</h3>\n<p><em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Judg3:15\">JDG 3:15</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Judg3:17-Judg3:18\">JDG 3:17–3:18</a></p>\n<h3>David, from the Moabites</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Sam8:2\">2SA 8:2</a></strong> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Chr18:2\">1CH 18:2</a></p>\n<h3>David, from the Arameans</h3>\n<p><em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Sam8:6\">2SA 8:6</a> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Chr18:6\">1CH 18:6</a></p>\n<h3>Solomon, from all the lands</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Kgs4:21\">1KI 4:21</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezra4:20\">EZR 4:20</a></p>\n<h3>Ben-Hadad's demands from Ahab</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Kgs20:2-1Kgs20:9\">1KI 20:2–20:9</a></p>\n<h3>Ahab, from the king of Moab</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Kgs3:4\">2KI 3:4</a></p>\n<h3>Isaiah's advice to Moab</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa16:1-Isa16:2\">ISA 16:1–16:2</a></p>\n<h3>Jehoshaphat, from the Philistines and Arabs</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Chr17:11\">2CH 17:11</a></p>\n<h3>Uzziah, from the Ammonites</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Chr26:8\">2CH 26:8</a></p>\n<h3>Jotham, from the Ammonites</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Chr27:5\">2CH 27:5</a></p>\n<h3>The Assyrian kings, from Israel</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Kgs15:19-2Kgs15:20\">2KI 15:19–15:20</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Kgs17:3-2Kgs17:4\">2KI 17:3–17:4</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Hos10:5-Hos10:6\">HOS 10:5–10:6</a></p>\n<h3>Pharaoh Neco, from Jehoiakim</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Kgs23:35\">2KI 23:35</a></p>\n<h3>Babylonian plunder</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Kgs24:13\">2KI 24:13</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Chr36:18\">2CH 36:18</a></p>\n<h3>Artaxerxes, from the Jews</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezra4:13\">EZR 4:13</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezra7:24\">EZR 7:24</a></p>\n<h3>Xerxes, from the whole empire</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Esth10:1\">EST 10:1</a></p>\n<h3>Roman taxes</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt22:17\">MAT 22:17</a> parallels <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark12:14\">MRK 12:14</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke20:22\">LUK 20:22</a></p>\n<h2>Tribute paid to those in authority</h2>\n<h3>David</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Sam9:6\">2SA 9:6</a></p>\n<h3>Daniel</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Dan2:46\">DAN 2:46</a></p>\n<h3>Haman</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Esth3:2\">EST 3:2</a></p>\n<h3>Herod</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts12:21-Acts12:23\">ACT 12:21–12:23</a></p>\n<h2>Tribute in the form of praise</h2>\n<h3>David, of Saul and Jonathan</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Sam1:23-2Sam1:27\">2SA 1:23–1:27</a></p>\n<h3>Paul, of faithful friends</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom16:3-Rom16:13\">ROM 16:3–16:13</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Cor8:22-2Cor8:24\">2CO 8:22–8:24</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Phil2:19-Phil2:30\">PHP 2:19–2:30</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Col4:7-Col4:14\">COL 4:7–4:14</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Tim1:16-2Tim1:18\">2TI 1:16–1:18</a></p>\n<h3>John, of Demetrius</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/3John1:12\">3JN 1:12</a></p>\n<h2>Christian principles on paying tribute</h2>\n<h3>OT teaching</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Prov24:21-Prov24:22\">PRO 24:21–24:22</a></p>\n<h3>Jesus Christ's teaching</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt22:21\">MAT 22:21</a></strong> parallels <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark12:17\">MRK 12:17</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke20:25\">LUK 20:25</a></p>\n<h3>Apostolic teaching</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom13:7\">ROM 13:7</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Pet2:17\">1PE 2:17</a></p>\n<h2>Tribute due to Jesus Christ</h2>\n<h3>Prophesied in the OT</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps72:10-Ps72:11\">PSA 72:10–72:11</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps89:22\">PSA 89:22</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa52:15\">ISA 52:15</a></p>\n<h3>Due because of his exaltation</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Phil2:9-Phil2:11\">PHP 2:9–2:11</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa45:23\">ISA 45:23</a></p>\n<h3>Fulfilled in the New Jerusalem</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev21:24\">REV 21:24</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev21:26\">REV 21:26</a></strong></p>",
